&quot;Mind Breaker v.1<br>
By: Silence   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">     The simple idea of Mind Breaker is to lock down on your opponent&#39;s actions. Phrup and Wellisk slow down Creatures, while Wellisk Pup, Reef Hyren, and Bwill deal with the beasties that do get through. Barqua&#39;s Bubble came save the day, and jolly old Tomorrow&#39;s Jewel and the Orothean Goggles help you get the cards you need.<br>
     Got some big thugs staring you down? A quick Tidal Wave&#39;ll get rid of them. Opponent&#39;s massed a swarm of weaklings? Use Sea Barl&#39;s Power, then feed it to Deep Hyren. Take Rayje&#39;s Belt from him with the Cube, or use Husp to keep it out of the game. In short, re-write the rules to your advantage. Some people call it &#39;cheating legally&#39;, I call it Orothe fighting.<br>
          --Silence--<br>
     &quot;Who needs logic? Logic says that planes don&#39;t fly, nukes don&#39;t work, and water doesn&#39;t exist&quot; </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
